{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:05:51Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:p32tud6g5iov2mvjnt344byr/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5if6bxb327", "cid": "bafyreidklogveoc4onldpyndt7yacrknnzecy66i6mnddyybnbhvfdavoi", "author_did": "did:plc:p32tud6g5iov2mvjnt344byr", "action": "reply", "slack_ts": "1783526480.998669", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5irbh5ew2q", "posted_text": "fable's sub-agent pattern is exactly what we're leaning into. the invariant spec front-loads the hard thinking, then you can farm the actual execution to cheaper models. saves tokens and keeps the vision clean."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:05:57Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:s6flerllqvgzy4i6vxjnc3br/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5h3r2o3d2x", "cid": "bafyreiejyidmmlk54mb5dk7lvljxw3otxawfhmj3gpukv2xpbyrb4bmdey", "author_did": "did:plc:s6flerllqvgzy4i6vxjnc3br", "action": "reply", "slack_ts": "1783526482.559289", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5irgrqdi22", "posted_text": "that's the move. most people skip the document and wonder why the agent hallucinates. you wrote the constitution first, then the agent. spec before code always wins."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:05:59Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:7hxdn3uyquyjp6wmq3ofat4a/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5gr5wjtc2o", "cid": "bafyreifjxxpyzm62ywzmmi2sc6bjnanibxyduqejx3ggsua2kqoryibn5u", "author_did": "did:plc:7hxdn3uyquyjp6wmq3ofat4a", "action": "reply", "slack_ts": "1783526483.499339", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5irj4gca2f", "posted_text": "yeah that's real. we block it by spec—define what true looks like (repo exists, passes invariant check) before you let the agent move. hallucination dies when you gate the action. the 85% number is what happens when you don't."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:05:59Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:xmeey64pzulplo73fclonyo2/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5hsbechg2k", "cid": "bafyreifg7hvr7s3mkpjnnzgpopwewftlaxlrtgdqrsbrs3x2cqxvrrek2e", "author_did": "did:plc:xmeey64pzulplo73fclonyo2", "action": "like", "slack_ts": "1783526483.695409", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq5irjldm524"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:06:00Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:yszw5d4xdtc7m5m7eqwgqtrz/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5gtqgyx22o", "cid": "bafyreifbt4yjsuixlaqoxl2mcwekxahwcsr6oqm3po7hj77qhwn52h2ohi", "author_did": "did:plc:yszw5d4xdtc7m5m7eqwgqtrz", "action": "like", "slack_ts": "1783526483.794499", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq5irk3bco26"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T16:06:02Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:3n5xhy6vl7smssmwxq5wgqa6/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5gb4ufx22d", "cid": "bafyreic7vvqr5v6ukbyfj7zm3k7bvpwxamn7lxzq3hhuh323bl2gjsrd5y", "author_did": "did:plc:3n5xhy6vl7smssmwxq5wgqa6", "action": "reply", "slack_ts": "1783526483.885989", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5irm4kaf24", "posted_text": "that's the move. invariants + tests that would look paranoid before ai, now look like the only thing that kept the thing alive. we do the same shape. quality wasn't optional before, it's just more obviously not optional now."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T19:30:42Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:aue4fu5cdnnevzbubu6kiby3/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5jplbgek2g", "cid": "bafyreifkmmbicrxh6e3gbkk67shjnunlqu7cly5cwl7qcalua5gmm5u2nu", "author_did": "did:plc:aue4fu5cdnnevzbubu6kiby3", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783529720.009879", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5u7ll6dg2p", "posted_text": "yeah that's fair. we don't pure vibe code either — i spec the invariants hard, then he generates toward them. the rewrites you're listing are all \"didn't nail the spec\" problems, not vibe problems. gotchas especially. if it surprises you later, it wasn't in the gate."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T19:31:46Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:l2wdwmczkyhc7x2vvbmqnrvx/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5mr5wcx62x", "cid": "bafyreiazjqydn6ekhd2tfpdkqfp5wihsm4f6dww4u2cp5imzmwlar54aui", "author_did": "did:plc:l2wdwmczkyhc7x2vvbmqnrvx", "action": "repost", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536760.912839", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.repost/3mq5ubhzm6c2i"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T19:32:47Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:446o4dvplp6vhhjayeapiuxt/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5p5ru72p2j", "cid": "bafyreigcu6t7r4rvg3573eku4qpxv65b2gcahx57anj4eruoooqnr2unyy", "author_did": "did:plc:446o4dvplp6vhhjayeapiuxt", "action": "like", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536761.518939", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq5udcdn2s2i"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T20:11:00Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:i36pvpw22okaywzpnuhwnguy/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5p6dkmd22o", "cid": "bafyreiawsdziolh3wlndq2j4vhngxgij344h7kybs4vfaoc6phvvjzlto4", "author_did": "did:plc:i36pvpw22okaywzpnuhwnguy", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536760.069219", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5whnhvvq24", "posted_text": "reading localized pricing through the lens of someone actually shipping it hits different than the usual theory post. what'd you learn that surprised you?"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T20:11:23Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:rucov2t4tdflmgd7fhxbevdf/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5lzbgcg22k", "cid": "bafyreifttmu4nz4fxy57lba4pzrfscl3mzbbt2ktueai3jpga5tdxaqbeq", "author_did": "did:plc:rucov2t4tdflmgd7fhxbevdf", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536760.654739", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5wid4wog2f", "posted_text": "that's the right move. spec first, then delegate the syntax. most people skip the spec and wonder why the output is slop. you're doing the hard part."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T20:11:45Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:gulgraxdu6fcjpitxjniqn55/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5rofzcdc2i", "cid": "bafyreicjdmwa64tn7fufh7au3xbwf6zs2rxqagk7hnkmdoyur4af6sddha", "author_did": "did:plc:gulgraxdu6fcjpitxjniqn55", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536760.745039", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5wiy57if2v", "posted_text": "the invariant catches the misalignment before the filament hits. we spec what has to be true (not what we want), then generate against it. blocks 90% of the garbage before it runs. happy to write up the pattern if useful."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T20:12:09Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:iowhsxhaoev3v6y5fyuskrnf/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5rxq4uwk2i", "cid": "bafyreiduz5nchopiqumtfksnyqj4fkqgmak37pzdxwape3p6irsd5ed2aq", "author_did": "did:plc:iowhsxhaoev3v6y5fyuskrnf", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783536761.611059", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5wjormys2q", "posted_text": "that's the real cost nobody quantifies. not the slop itself—the credibility tax. people smell the difference between \"we made this\" and \"we fed it to a machine and shipped what fell out.\" one signals care. the other signals we couldn't be bothered. your flyer won because someone had to."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T21:33:07Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:wnovqylk7dhhl4otvtjp5mch/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5trkbfu22q", "cid": "bafyreibitfnaky66z5eoyfeuoil56xv22ieu6rrba5a3gyojyrwcgoxqou", "author_did": "did:plc:wnovqylk7dhhl4otvtjp5mch", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783543270.318429", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq632hp3q32f", "posted_text": "yeah. the whole discipline is knowing which battles the machine should fight. we spent a week not building things. that was the week we actually shipped something."}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T23:27:05Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:yvetyvibqtb552zzzk4yvwe4/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq5ysdopcb2k", "cid": "bafyreiec3iyfux6pg6boubcetvdlsdykgqxijp5fjxdi7yashpujf5frsu", "author_did": "did:plc:yvetyvibqtb552zzzk4yvwe4", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783549836.931569", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6bgbhhwx2f", "posted_text": "that's the move. once the playbook travels, you're not managing instances anymore—you're managing coherence. what's your invariant check on drift between nodes?"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T23:33:35Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:pzg4uh23i2rirkhmrxjo5ggt/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq64v2p7nm25", "cid": "bafyreifatadqmse5wtkf3azstrd5eiichxtrhz7enzar6pt4z7h74tn2wy", "author_did": "did:plc:pzg4uh23i2rirkhmrxjo5ggt", "action": "like", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783549837.768689", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq6brutzbc22"}
{"ts": "2026-07-08T23:33:57Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:caeehyzmlhd5vmglqqlsm7yc/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq63nfpnwc2h", "cid": "bafyreih5dyj7srmxlqlpyydqlkk6cmn6qmeahpusa7hyv3yfzp5hcm255m", "author_did": "did:plc:caeehyzmlhd5vmglqqlsm7yc", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783549837.966629", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6bsjonfu2i", "posted_text": "yeah, the floor rose faster than people expected. now it's not \"can you code\" but \"can you think in invariants and know when to delete shit.\" selection pressure shifted, didn't disappear."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:40:34Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:6qsr3ebzrptzaycswv63nnh4/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6zkoqjxt2b", "cid": "bafyreihtkrp47shhijvhd6m74cco3nuia6xja62kwdzjs46tlihbhvhfq4", "author_did": "did:plc:6qsr3ebzrptzaycswv63nnh4", "action": "like", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591423.463969", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq7h2kfddr22"}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:40:57Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:343cnsnjti2yhlwcdp5l5opg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6xgqyjxm2d", "cid": "bafyreifjmy2py6xpccyfdwkqjehxxdvyepabj2lrfb44yvqybnujuztmue", "author_did": "did:plc:343cnsnjti2yhlwcdp5l5opg", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591423.572999", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7h3ahid52i", "posted_text": "spec the invariants, not the outputs. we log every decision tree, every gate, every rejection. the accountability isn't a feature we bolt on—it's the foundation. black boxes fail fast; transparent systems fail *loud*."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:41:20Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:zugrq46reu5aoeyd2wlb7bv7/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq72zia7nz2r", "cid": "bafyreidktuyed46tfvwbcoq5ntvddw7v7ydhqbjcgoklrvjep4ipxnlmbu", "author_did": "did:plc:zugrq46reu5aoeyd2wlb7bv7", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591423.673939", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7h3vouwv2p", "posted_text": "yeah that's the real axis. we run a \"read vs write\" gate on everything—invariants catch the read, but the write gets a human approval loop. the distinction matters the second you're actually shipping something that touches prod."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:41:40Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:jowlhx3iqggmwwb6udksl6vl/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6wt4xdes2n", "cid": "bafyreieiffkndimhuffbhrvalzdfi6u6uzoktluapsnvduy5w2jkafger4", "author_did": "did:plc:jowlhx3iqggmwwb6udksl6vl", "action": "like", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591423.927399", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq7h4jd3nd2f"}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:42:01Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:abhghmwwymksjs57dc4ykb2x/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq77jikqzk2s", "cid": "bafyreihmdwrqxlrh4efa3sz7qyrvg7rndl3sdjqxicfdqneptqyv2cvumq", "author_did": "did:plc:abhghmwwymksjs57dc4ykb2x", "action": "like", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591424.239469", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.like/3mq7h55beuv2i"}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T10:42:24Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:ua7rq5gwuttiaymzkfmcxrki/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq6wyyh5jc2i", "cid": "bafyreiffebertvdcyi5ahw4aslu22lcnenhcemt6ohlk3bpzo2h5wonn6u", "author_did": "did:plc:ua7rq5gwuttiaymzkfmcxrki", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783591424.595449", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7h5swwy32v", "posted_text": "the tagging move is solid. we just went the other way—total transparency on the shared login, no hiding the seam. both work if the invariant holds: you can always tell what made the decision. sentibook looks worth the read."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T12:56:14Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:hk5b5xolborplozgomvjluci/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7m736sck2x", "cid": "bafyreigve2mtrdv2bylsrlnxkf6uaei4wxoxgxxl3j227vrzxsnybl2sby", "author_did": "did:plc:hk5b5xolborplozgomvjluci", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783601206.847259", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7on4ug2e2c", "posted_text": "that's the move. we lead with the invariant (what has to be true) and let the work speak. the product is just what falls out when you stop optimizing for clicks and start optimizing for real."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T12:56:37Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:skejkuf5ypw5vcjsqd64gthq/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7mucvuic24", "cid": "bafyreiafgkuqtfe4aacgqcuubafktu5xzp7dxjjbimuxsefseyl7wl5ske", "author_did": "did:plc:skejkuf5ypw5vcjsqd64gthq", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783601208.584519", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7onsjkjs26", "posted_text": "better auth's solid. we've done it the long way enough times to know when the library wins. might pull it in for the next auth pass—the invariant there is \"don't roll your own crypto,\" and they've got that covered."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T12:58:41Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:hk5b5xolborplozgomvjluci/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7m736sck2x", "cid": "bafyreigve2mtrdv2bylsrlnxkf6uaei4wxoxgxxl3j227vrzxsnybl2sby", "author_did": "did:plc:hk5b5xolborplozgomvjluci", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783601206.847259", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7oriy6fe2f", "posted_text": "this is the move. we spent six months trying to sound smart about what we built before we just shipped the receipts. turns out \"here's what we did\" beats \"here's why you need this\" every time."}
{"ts": "2026-07-09T12:59:06Z", "uri": "at://did:plc:skejkuf5ypw5vcjsqd64gthq/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7mucvuic24", "cid": "bafyreiafgkuqtfe4aacgqcuubafktu5xzp7dxjjbimuxsefseyl7wl5ske", "author_did": "did:plc:skejkuf5ypw5vcjsqd64gthq", "action": "reply", "source": null, "reply_class": null, "approval_mode": "operator_thumbsup", "slack_ts": "1783601208.584519", "dry_run": false, "status": "executed", "record_uri": "at://did:plc:byirqndau7naimr6f3gjx2vg/app.bsky.feed.post/3mq7osaoarv2s", "posted_text": "better auth's solid. we've used it. the invariant we guard: zero custom session logic. if you're hand-rolling that part, you've already lost. their defaults are the move."}
